This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks such as semantic segmentation and object detection, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new layer that can be integrated into deep neural networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The paper also discusses the use of statistical features and deep learning methods, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The use of back-propagation and joint optimization further suggests that it may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper's focus on visual data and deep learning could also place it in the cs.MM (Multimedia) category.
